This bug was firstly found in BIRT (http://www.eclipse.org/birt/phoenix/), and we traced the codes until we found that in this case, the implementation of org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Tree towards Mac cause the bug.

When user selects and drags an object and move it still in the source View, and if the View is a Treeview, the method "getSelection()" in Tree will set the selected object as "null". Subsquently, it causes drop nothing onto the destination.

We have fixed this bug by modifying codes in BIRT. However, we would still like to konw the thinking on this issue from you guys. Thanks.

Steps to reproduce:
1.Download BIRT 2.1.0 release;
2.Start up BIRT in Mac OS X;
3.File->New->Project;
4.File->New->Report Design;
5.In Data Explorer, create a New Data Source, and choose "Classic Models Inc. Sample DataBase", press "Next" and then press "finish";
6.In Data Explorer, create a New Data Set, press "Next";
7.In the popup window, expand the "CLASSICMODELS", select and drag any item onto 
right side.

OR
1.Start up BIRT in Mac OS X;
2.Open a report design file (in attachment);
3.Select a data set in Data Exporer and expand it;
4.Select and drag a item under of Data Set onto Layout editor at the right side;

Expect result:
Drop the selected item.
Actual result:
Drop nothing.

